paragraph
 PL/0 is a programming language, intended as an educational programming language, that is similar to but much simpler than Pascal, a general-purpose programming language. It serves as an example of how to construct a compiler. It was originally introduced in the book, Algorithms + Data Structures = Programs, by Niklaus Wirth in 1976. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PL/0">Read more on Wikipedia...</a>

